Look, Mr. Jefferies, I'm not an educated woman, but I can tell you one thing:
我没读过什么书，但我可以告诉你

164
00:12:56,190 --> 00:12:59,490
When a man and a woman see each other and like each other,
如果两个人一见钟情

165
00:12:59,490 --> 00:13:01,590
they ought to come together, wham,
他们就该砰地一声撞在一起，

166
00:13:01,690 --> 00:13:03,590
like a couple of taxis on Broadway...
就像路上的两辆的士

167
00:13:03,690 --> 00:13:06,290
and not sit around analyzing each other...
而不是坐着，像标本一样，彼此分析

168
00:13:06,490 --> 00:13:08,390
like two specimens in a bottle.

169
00:13:08,490 --> 00:13:11,490
There's an intelligent way to approach marriage.
对婚姻来说，这可不理智

170
00:13:11,590 --> 00:13:13,490
Intelligence.
理智？

171
00:13:13,590 --> 00:13:16,690
Nothing has caused the human race so much trouble as intelligence.
没有比“理智”更容易招惹麻烦的了

172
00:13:16,790 --> 00:13:19,190
Modern marriage.
所谓的现代婚姻

173
00:13:19,290 --> 00:13:23,090
We've progressed emotionally. Baloney.
我们在情感上更成熟了

174
00:13:23,190 --> 00:13:27,390
Once it was see somebody, get excited, get married.
胡扯

175
00:13:23,302 --> 00:13:27,138
以前的人只要见个面，觉得心动，就结婚

176
00:13:27,490 --> 00:13:29,490
Now, it's read a lot of books,
现在呢，读一大堆书，

177
00:13:29,590 --> 00:13:33,290
fence with a lot of four-syllable words, psychoanalyze each other...
用复杂的术语相互分析

178
00:13:33,390 --> 00:13:35,290
until you can't tell the difference...
直到你们不能区分彼此

179
00:13:35,390 --> 00:13:38,290
between a petting party and a civil service exam.
搞得亲热聚会像公务员考试一样

180
00:13:38,390 --> 00:13:42,090
People have different emotional levels...
人们的情商各不相同

181
00:13:42,190 --> 00:13:45,790
When I married Myles, we were both a couple of maladjusted misfits.
我和迈尔斯结婚时，就有性格差异

182
00:13:45,890 --> 00:13:51,090
We are still maladjusted, and we have loved every minute of it.
现在还是这样，但我们珍惜在一起的每一刻

183
00:13:51,190 --> 00:13:54,590
That's fine, Stella. Now, would you fix me a sandwich, please?
真好，斯泰拉，你能帮我做个三明治吗？

184
00:13:54,690 --> 00:13:58,790
Yes, I will. And I'll spread a little common sense on the bread.
好的，我要在面包上面涂点“常识”

185
00:13:58,890 --> 00:14:01,790
Lisa's loaded to her fingertips with love for you.
丽莎非常爱你

186
00:14:01,890 --> 00:14:04,790
I got two words of advice for you: Marry her.
听我一句，娶她吧

187
00:14:04,890 --> 00:14:07,590
- She pay you much? - Oh.
- 她付你多少钱？ - 噢

188
00:14:24,590 --> 00:14:26,590
There you are.
好了

189
00:14:29,490 --> 00:14:31,790
- Here's the key. - Thank you.
- 这是钥匙 - 多谢

190
00:14:39,690 --> 00:14:43,090
If you want anything, just ring.
有什么需要就按铃

191
00:14:55,490 --> 00:14:58,390
Come on over here. Come on.
过来，来吧

192
00:15:31,090 --> 00:15:33,190
Window shopper.
偷窥高手

193
00:16:22,190 --> 00:16:24,490
How's your leg?
-腿怎样了？

194
00:16:24,590 --> 00:16:26,490
It hurts a little.
还有点痛

195
00:16:26,590 --> 00:16:30,490
- And your stomach? - Empty as a football.
- 肚子呢？ -空得像个足球

196
00:16:32,390 --> 00:16:34,490
And your love life?
你的爱情生活呢？

197
00:16:34,590 --> 00:16:37,190
Not too active.
一般

198
00:16:37,390 --> 00:16:39,990
Anything else bothering you?
有什么困扰吗？

199
00:16:39,990 --> 00:16:41,990
Mm-hmm.

200
00:16:42,090 --> 00:16:44,090
Who are you?
你是谁？

201
00:16:45,990 --> 00:16:48,190
Reading from top to bottom:
看仔细了，

202
00:16:48,290 --> 00:16:50,190
Lisa...
丽莎

203
00:16:53,190 --> 00:16:55,090
Carol...
卡洛

204
00:16:59,190 --> 00:17:01,490
Fremont.
弗里蒙特

205
00:17:01,590 --> 00:17:05,290
Is this the Lisa Fremont who never wears the same dress twice?
这个就是从不把一条裙子穿两遍的丽莎？

206
00:17:05,390 --> 00:17:07,790
Only because it's expected of her.
这是专门订做的

207
00:17:07,890 --> 00:17:10,290
It's right off the Paris plane.
刚刚从法国用飞机运来

208
00:17:10,390 --> 00:17:13,590
- Do you think it'll sell? - That depends on the quote.
-你觉得会畅销吗？ -那得看价格如何

209
00:17:13,690 --> 00:17:18,090
Let's see now. There's the airplane ticket over and import duties, hidden taxes,
你看，得加上航空运费、关税、间接费用和利润

210
00:17:18,190 --> 00:17:21,190
profit markup... A steal at $ 1,100.
1,100美元，很划算

211
00:17:21,190 --> 00:17:26,190
Eleven hundred? They ought to list that dress on the stock exchange.
1,100？应该把它送到股票交易所去上市

212
00:17:26,290 --> 00:17:29,290
We sell a dozen a day in this price range.
我们今天卖了12件，都是这个价

213
00:17:29,290 --> 00:17:30,990
Who buys them, tax collectors?
谁买的？ 收税的？

214
00:17:30,990 --> 00:17:33,090
Even if I had to pay, it would be worth it,
即使让我自己付钱，也值得

215
00:17:33,190 --> 00:17:36,490
- just for the occasion. - Something big going on somewhere?
-只在重要场合穿 -有什么重要的晚会吗？

216
00:17:37,090 --> 00:17:39,390
It's going on right here. It's a big night.
就在这儿，今晚

217
00:17:39,390 --> 00:17:42,490
It's just an old run-of-the-mill Wednesday.
这只是一个普通的周三晚上

218
00:17:42,590 --> 00:17:44,390
The calender's full of them.
日历上有的是

219
00:17:44,490 --> 00:17:49,590
It's opening night of the last depressing week of L.B. Jefferies in a cast.
今晚是“L.B.杰弗利戴石膏的最后沮丧一周”公开首演

220
00:17:49,590 --> 00:17:53,390
Well, I haven't noticed a big demand for tickets.
呃，我没看到有人买票

221
00:17:53,490 --> 00:17:56,390
That's because I bought out the house.
那是因为今晚我包场了

222
00:17:56,390 --> 00:18:00,290
You know, this cigarette box has seen better days.
这盒烟曾经风麾一时

223
00:18:00,390 --> 00:18:03,790
I picked that up in Shanghai, which has also seen better days.
我在上海买的，那地方也曾风麾一时

224
00:18:03,890 --> 00:18:06,190
It's cracked and you never use it.
都裂了，你从没用过它

225
00:18:06,290 --> 00:18:08,290
It's too ornate.
它太奢华了

226
00:18:08,390 --> 00:18:11,790
I'm sending up a plain, flat, silver one with your initials.
我送个普通的银烟盒给你，刻上你的名字

227
00:18:11,890 --> 00:18:14,590
That's no way to spend your hard-earned money.
我可不想花你的辛苦钱

228
00:18:14,590 --> 00:18:17,090
I wanted to.
我愿意

229
00:18:17,190 --> 00:18:19,290
Ooh!

230
00:18:19,390 --> 00:18:22,490
What would you think of starting off with dinner at 21?
你觉得共进一顿“21号”餐厅的美味晚餐如何？

231
00:18:22,690 --> 00:18:25,390
You have, perhaps, an ambulance downstairs?
你把救护车叫来了？

232
00:18:25,490 --> 00:18:29,390
No, better than that: 21.
不，比那更好，“21号”餐厅

233
00:18:34,190 --> 00:18:37,190
Thank you for waiting, Carl. The kitchen's right there on the left.
多谢你了，卡尔，厨房在左边

234
00:18:37,290 --> 00:18:39,390
I'll take the wine.
我来拿酒

235
00:18:41,590 --> 00:18:43,590
- Good evening, Mr. Jefferies. - Carl.
-晚上好，杰弗利先生 -卡尔

236
00:18:43,590 --> 00:18:47,090
- Just put everything in the oven on low. - Yes, madame.
-把东西放炉里子里就行了 -好的，女士

237
00:18:47,090 --> 00:18:49,690
- Let's open the wine now. - All right.
-我们来开酒 -好吧

238
00:18:49,790 --> 00:18:53,390
- It's a Montrachet. - A great big glassful.
-是蒙拉谢(酒名) -要用大杯子

239
00:18:53,490 --> 00:18:56,190
There's a corkscrew right over there.
那儿有开瓶器，

240
00:18:56,290 --> 00:18:58,190
Here, I'll do it.
让我来

241
00:19:00,090 --> 00:19:02,190
- Big enough? - Yeah, fine.
-够大吗？ -够了

242
00:19:02,290 --> 00:19:06,190
I can't think of anything more boring or tiresome than what you've been through.
我想不出比被困在家里更泛味，无聊的事了

243
00:19:06,290 --> 00:19:08,990
- and the last week must be the hardest. - Let me, sir.
-上周肯定是最难熬的 -让我来吧，先生

244
00:19:08,990 --> 00:19:12,990
All right. Yeah, I want to get this thing off and get moving.
好吧，是呀，我真想把这东西弄掉，好好活动活动

245
00:19:12,990 --> 00:19:17,290
I'm going to make this a week you'll never forget.
我要把这周变成最你难忘的一周

246
00:19:19,390 --> 00:19:21,290
Fine, thanks.
好的，谢谢

247
00:19:21,390 --> 00:19:23,590
Just a minute, Carl.
等一下，卡尔

248
00:19:23,690 --> 00:19:26,990
- This will take care of the taxi as well. - Thank you, Miss Fremont.
打的士的钱也在里面了

249
00:19:26,990 --> 00:19:30,290
- Have a pleasant dinner, Mr. Jefferies. - All right. Good night.
-谢谢你，弗里蒙特小姐，祝您用餐愉快，杰弗利先生 -好的，晚安

250
00:19:30,390 --> 00:19:32,290
Good night.
晚安

251
00:19:34,190 --> 00:19:36,290
What a day I've had.
今天可真忙呀 

252
00:19:36,390 --> 00:19:38,490
- Are you tired? - Not a bit.
- 你累了 - 点也不

253
00:19:38,490 --> 00:19:40,590
I was all morning in a meeting,
整个上午都在和CEO开会，

254
00:19:40,690 --> 00:19:44,290
then I had to dash to the Waldorf for a quick drink with Madame Dufrene...
然后赶去见杜弗兰太太

255
00:19:44,290 --> 00:19:47,790
who's just over from Paris with some spy reports.
她刚从巴黎带回一些商业信息

256
00:19:48,390 --> 00:19:52,790
I had to go to 21 and have lunch with the Harper's Bazaar people.
然后又去“21号”餐厅和代理商吃午餐

257
00:19:52,890 --> 00:19:54,890
That's when I ordered dinner.
于是我在那儿订了晚餐

258
00:19:54,990 --> 00:19:57,790
Then I had two fall showings 20 blocks apart.
然后又连开了两场秋季服装展示会

259
00:19:57,890 --> 00:20:00,390
Then I had to have a cocktail with Leland and Slim Hayward.
又与利兰和海沃德一起喝鸡尾酒，

260
00:20:00,490 --> 00:20:02,390
We're trying to get his new show.
我们准备为他开一个新的发布会

261
00:20:02,490 --> 00:20:04,390
Then I had to dash back and change.
接着赶回来换衣服

262
00:20:04,490 --> 00:20:08,890
Now, tell me, what was Mrs. Hayward wearing?
告诉我，海沃德太太穿的什么

263
00:20:09,090 --> 00:20:10,990
- She looked wonderfully cool. - She did?
她看上去太漂亮了，

264
00:20:11,090 --> 00:20:14,010
She had on the most divine Italian hand-printed... 
她穿着上等的意大利手工印制的…

265
00:20:14,142 --> 00:20:16,060
Oh, Italian?
噢，意大利的？ [嘲讽的语气]

266
00:20:16,090 --> 00:20:18,190
Oh, you. Italian. Imagine.
-是意大利的，想想看 -噢，你…

267
00:20:18,290 --> 00:20:20,390
To think I planted three nice items...
我今天在报纸上用了三个专题来介绍你

268
00:20:20,390 --> 00:20:22,490
- ...in the columns about you today. - You did?
- 真的？

269
00:20:22,590 --> 00:20:25,990
- You can't buy that kind of publicity. - I know.
- 知名度是钱买不到的 - 我知道

270
00:20:26,090 --> 00:20:29,990
Someday you may want to open up a studio of your own here.
有一天，你也许想在这里开个自己的工作室

271
00:20:30,090 --> 00:20:33,990
How would I run it from, say, Pakistan?
我怎么顾得过来？如果我在，比如说，巴基斯坦

272
00:20:34,090 --> 00:20:36,690
Jeff...
杰夫，

273
00:20:36,790 --> 00:20:39,190
isn't it time you came home?
别再四处奔波了

274
00:20:39,290 --> 00:20:41,190
You could pick your assignment.
你可以自己挑选工作

275
00:20:42,590 --> 00:20:45,190
- I wish there was one I wanted. - Make the one you want.
-希望有我喜欢的 -那就创造一个

276
00:20:45,190 --> 00:20:47,190
- You mean leave the magazine? - Yes.
- 你是说离开杂志社？ - 对

277
00:20:47,190 --> 00:20:51,490
- For what? - For yourself and me.
- 为什么？ - 为了你和我

278
00:20:51,590 --> 00:20:53,790
I could get you a dozen assignments tomorrow:
我可以提供一打工作让你挑选

279
00:20:53,890 --> 00:20:55,790
fashions, portraits.
时尚杂志、人物摄影

280
00:20:55,890 --> 00:20:59,490
- Now, don't laugh. I could do it. - That's what I'm afraid of.
- 别笑，我是认真的 - 那才是我害怕的

281
00:20:59,590 --> 00:21:02,790
Can you see me driving down to the fashion salon in a jeep...
你能想像我开着吉普车，装着军靴

282
00:21:02,890 --> 00:21:05,290
wearing combat boots and a three-day beard?
胡子邋遢地去参加时尚沙龙吗？

283
00:21:05,390 --> 00:21:07,290
Wouldn't that make a hit?
能行吗？

284
00:21:07,390 --> 00:21:10,390
I could see you looking very handsome and successful...
我能想像，你会是个英俊的...

285
00:21:10,490 --> 00:21:12,490
in a dark blue flannel suit.
身着法兰绒西装的成功人士

286
00:21:12,590 --> 00:21:17,790
Let's stop talking nonsense, shall we? Hmm?
我们别说废话了，好吗？

287
00:21:19,290 --> 00:21:22,690
Guess I'd better start setting up for dinner.
我还是去准备晚饭吧

